## Installation

The Svelte package does not currently export a `PageHeader` block or a block-install CLI. Compose the pattern from `Breadcrumbs`, `Tabs`, and `Button`, or copy the demo shell below into your application and adapt it.

## Usage

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import { Breadcrumbs, BreadcrumbsCurrent, BreadcrumbsLink, BreadcrumbsSeparator, Button, Tabs } from "kumo-svelte";

  const tabs = [
    { label: "Overview", value: "overview" },
    { label: "Settings", value: "settings" },
  ];
</script>

<header class="rounded-lg border border-kumo-hairline bg-kumo-base">
  <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 p-4">
    <Breadcrumbs>
      <BreadcrumbsLink href="#">Home</BreadcrumbsLink>
      <BreadcrumbsSeparator />
      <BreadcrumbsCurrent>My Project</BreadcrumbsCurrent>
    </Breadcrumbs>
    <Button variant="primary" size="sm">Deploy</Button>
  </div>
  <div class="border-t border-kumo-hairline px-4 py-3">
    <Tabs {tabs} selectedValue="overview" />
  </div>
</header>
```

