## API Reference

Because the Svelte library does not yet ship this block as an exported component, there is no package API to document. Use the demo shell as a starting point.

### Suggested props

| Prop | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `breadcrumbs` | `Snippet` | Breadcrumb navigation shown at the top left. |
| `title` | `string` | Optional page title. |
| `description` | `string` | Optional page description. |
| `tabs` | `TabsItem[]` | Optional tab definitions passed to `Tabs`. |
| `actions` | `Snippet` | Optional action buttons shown on the right. |

## Svelte Notes

The upstream React block receives React nodes for `breadcrumbs` and `children`. The Svelte equivalent uses snippets or direct composition, and the tabs are passed to the Svelte `Tabs` component.
